# Core rules (ONAT Angular)

- Keep diffs small and consistent with existing patterns; do not “re-architect” unless asked.
- Do not add new dependencies or change build tooling unless explicitly required; explain impact when touching `angular.json`/`tsconfig*`/`package.json`.
- Prefer Angular 21 patterns already used here: **standalone components**, `inject()`, **signals**, and template control flow (`@if`, etc.).
- Follow formatting defaults used in this repo: Prettier `printWidth: 100`, `singleQuote: true`, and Angular HTML formatting.
- When changing behavior, update/adjust call sites and related UI/state flows so the feature remains coherent.
- Avoid redundant comments; only comment for non-obvious intent or constraints.
